{"comments":"Core mathematical functions — PURE PURESCRIPT.\n\nNo JavaScript. No FFI. Pure functional implementations using:\n- Taylor series for transcendental functions\n- Newton-Raphson iteration for roots\n- CORDIC-inspired algorithms where appropriate\n\n## Precision\n\nAll Taylor series use sufficient terms for IEEE 754 double precision\n(approximately 15-17 significant decimal digits).\n\n## Verification\n\nThese implementations have corresponding Lean4 proofs in:\n`proofs/Hydrogen/Math/Core.lean`\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Pi (ratio of circumference to diameter)\nComputed to full IEEE 754 double precision\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[109,13],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Math/Core.purs","start":[109,1]},"title":"pi"},{"children":[],"comments":"Euler's number (base of natural logarithm)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[113,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Math/Core.purs","start":[113,1]},"title":"e"},{"children":[],"comments":"Tau (2 * pi, full circle in radians)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[117,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Math/Core.purs","start":[117,1]},"title":"tau"},{"children":[],"comments":"Square root of 2\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[121,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Math/Core.purs","start":[121,1]},"title":"sqrt2"},{"children":[],"comments":"Square root of 1/2 (equivalently, 1/sqrt(2))\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[125,18],"name":"../../h